                            <comment id="12969482" author="nspiegelberg" created="Wed, 8 Dec 2010 20:47:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@jgray : note that, while adding the max compact threshold, we also made this value configurable &amp;amp; lowered the default value to flushSize * 1.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12969491" author="streamy" created="Wed, 8 Dec 2010 21:11:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hmm ok.  i think having this configurable is fairly important for 0.90 based on the behavior i saw on cluster.  i will update the config param name to whatever you used in the other patch and apply this only to the 90 branch (it will be picked up in next RC or 0.90.1).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12969495" author="streamy" created="Wed, 8 Dec 2010 21:17:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changes param name to be same as in trunk and changes default to 1X instead of 1.5X to match trunk.  This patch is for branch only.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12969511" author="stack" created="Wed, 8 Dec 2010 21:51:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If we&apos;re talking bytes when we talk of base.hstore.compaction.min.size, then +1.  If we&apos;re talking number of files, -1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12969542" author="streamy" created="Wed, 8 Dec 2010 22:54:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;size, yes.  this patch just brings in configurable parameter that&apos;s already committed in latest nicolas compaction changes on trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12969559" author="stack" created="Wed, 8 Dec 2010 23:30:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 then&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
